<dl id="n12137e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12137e">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12137e"> 137(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> K kowtow</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">It is even more singular that the Mongolian imbeciles should not only love to sit like a Buddha but to sway the head, backwards and forwards, like a porcelain mandarin, whilst I have seen a baby Mongolian idiot prostrate himself in his cot, for hours at a time, <mark>doing the Kow-Tow</mark>. <small> F.G. Crookshank, <a name="MIOM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#MIOM"><cite title="source">The Mongol in Our Midst</cite></a> (1924) 43</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
